  80:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      * AIN1 = adc_current (current-sense input, via INA180A1 U2, gain
  81:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   20V/V per TI's Device Comparison table — SOT23-5, pinout A).
  82:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   IN+/IN- sense the voltage drop across shunt resistor R16 (in
  83:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   series on the +12V rail, before the rest of the board); OUT
  84:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   feeds AIN1 through R9 (0R per schematic — a series link/isolation
ARM GAS  C:\Users\DELL\AppData\Local\Temp\ccqtkz11.s 			page 9


  85:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   resistor, not the shunt itself).
  86:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   *** OPEN QUESTION, UNRESOLVED as of this commit — do not assume
  87:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   an answer: R16's actual resistance value has not been confirmed.
  88:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   User initially said "0 ohm" for this discussion, but Vout = Gain
  89:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   x I x R_shunt means R_shunt=0 would force AIN1's reading to 0V
  90:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   for any current — i.e. the current-sense channel would never
  91:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   read anything. This is very likely a mix-up with R9 (which
  92:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   legitimately is 0R on the schematic, but sits on the output
  93:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   side, not the shunt). User said they'd confirm this in a future
  94:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   conversation. Until R16's real value is confirmed:
  95:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *     - PGA left at ADS1115_PGA_TWO as a placeholder only, matching
  96:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *       AIN2 for now — NOT derived from any confirmed R16 value.
  97:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *     - Treat every AIN1/adc_current reading as unverified — do not
  98:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *       trust it for any real current measurement or safety logic
  99:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *       (e.g. overcurrent cutoff) until this is resolved.
 100:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *
 101:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      * AIN2 = adc_vol (voltage-sense input, 12V rail through a resistor
 102:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   divider: R14=100K top / R15=20K bottom per schematic, confirmed
 103:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   with user — the divider node feeds AIN2 directly).
 104:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   Vout = Vin * 20k/(100k+20k) = Vin/6 -> 2.0V at 12V nominal,
 105:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   2.5V at a 15V worst-case rail — comfortably under both this
 106:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   board's VDD (3.3V) and the ADS1115's absolute maximum analog
 107:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   input rating of VDD+0.3V=3.6V (Documents/ads1115.pdf, Absolute
 108:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   Maximum Ratings table). ADS1115_PGA_TWO (FSR +-2.048V) matches
 109:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****      *   this range well. */
 110:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h ****     ADS1115_T   ads1115;
 111:SynaptiX_FDK/board/sx_board.h **** }Board_t;
